name: Ammonium sulphate
desc: Ammonium sulfate fertilizer is a source of nitrogen and sulfur for plants, and it can also be used to lower soil pH in high-pH soils. It is applied to lawns, often at a rate of five pounds per 1,000 square feet, and should be watered in well after application. This fertilizer is especially useful for crops like onions and garlic, which have high nutrient demands.
